    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">Should I decant wine for Thanksgiving dinner?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Decanting isn't necessary for most Thanksgiving wine selections, since you'll likely be serving younger, approachable wines that don't need extensive aeration. However, if you're serving a special bottle of aged red wine or a tannic young wine, decant it 30-60 minutes before dinner. Focus your energy instead on proper serving temperatures: chill whites to 45-50°F and serve reds slightly cool at 60-65°F.</p>
